<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="26" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="27.[192,1440,898,986]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,302,898,922]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Ecology</emphasis>
. Lowland, montane, subalpine. Endogean. Wet forests (podocarp, broadleaf, beech) and scrublands. Shaded ground. Nocturnal; hides during the day under fallen branches, logs, well-embedded stones, and in moss. Gregarious.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[192,1440,1025,1082]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,297,1025,1049]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Biology</emphasis>
. Seasonality: October–May. Tenerals: March (WD). Predacious (based on mouthpart morphology).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[192,1068,1121,1146]" box="[192,1068,1121,1146]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,418,1121,1146]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Dispersal power</emphasis>
. Subapterous (incapable of flight). Moderate runner.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[192,1288,1185,1210]" box="[192,1288,1185,1210]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,493,1185,1209]" pageId="27" pageNumber="26">Collecting techniques</emphasis>
. Lifting branches, logs and stones; sifting moss; pitfall trapping.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
